 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Xuraz</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> "The cheap horse only gives a 25% speed increase"</P><P>Allow me to dispell that myth.  The cheap horse offers NO noticable increase in speed.  Dont believe me? Buy one and see for yourself.  I dont care what the data is out there, that horse at at or just a hair over newbie running speed.</P><P>Also, the slow increase/decrease in speed will annoy you if you are used to casting spells on the run.  They cause spell interrupts, for short distnaces will actually take you longer to get there.</P><P>If you want to buy a horse, I say go for it.  You pay the $13 a month for this game, do what's most fun for you.  Just dont buy in to all the pie in the sky stuff people spout about horses, they are a little bit overrated if you are getting them for anything besides looks.</P><P>Xuraz Xorthexia - <BR>Warlock<BR>Xegony Server<BR>Profile - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=72377" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=72377</a></P><P>"They call us walking corpses, unholy living dead.<BR>They had to lock us up, put us in their pretty jails." - The Misfits</font></td>
