 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Nefarietteeci</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Don't forget that Horses let you carry as much weight as you need with no slowed movement rate. You can camp Gornit and take the 10K copper all the way to the bank (assuming you can get through the doors). You won't need to destroy Fine Steel anymore (outdoors).</P><P>Just another of the many little benefits that come with a horse. </P><P>Again, as everyone has said, it's just a tool may or may not be worth it to you. I like it a lot, others find it a complete waste. Again, make sure you're fully CHR buffed when you buy it (110 or more). Costs about 1K more for a cool black one (low end).</P><P>To earn the $ I camped Gornit for about 6 weeks. On a good night, four to six hour session, I would pull down maybe 1,500 plat (as much as I could carry in plat and some gold), but I was getting XP for it too, so it was a double whammy. Might be too boring if he's green, though you could pull Seafuries too. And you have to be able to get the camp, which is almost always taken (then you can wait around and kill Seafuries until it opens up).</P><P>Hill giants are crazy camped on E'ci, and every time I pass through Rathe Mountains people are whining over OOC about KSing, quad kiting steals, etc., so I avoided it completely, though I understand it's good money.</P><P>I hate auctioning (though I love buying!), so trading was out for me, but is probably the quickest way to make money.</P><P>Now I need to start saving up for an upgrade, but 100K is more cash than I'm likely to see in my lifetime.</P><P> </font></td>
